name: Squats
details: This is a squat done while holding a weight in front of you (like a goblet), which adds more of a workout for your core and legs and also makes getting into the correct squat form much easier

name: Leg Press
details: This “anti-rotation” movement is challenging because you must resist rotation forcing your obliques, abs, lower back, and glutes to do the work.

name: Dumbbell Row
details: The Dumbbell Row helps develop a strong back, arms and core. Plus, because it works your lats, traps, and rhomboids, it supports proper posture by pulling your shoulders back and helping to stabilize your spine.

name: Push-Ups
details: Push-Ups are a deceptively simple functional movement that works your upper-body muscles while engaging your core and allowing you to use the full range of motion in your shoulder blades

name: Lateral Squats
details: These are a combination of a lateral lunge and a squat, useful for stretching your groin and inner thighs while also targeting your hips, thighs, and core

name: Glute Bridges
details: This exercise helps train your glutes, which are often underutilized if you sit for long periods each day.
